ckButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2528752\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 03, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104ixk1665702772151.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ixk1665702772151.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ixk1665702772151.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"ixk1665702772151\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Generating and Compiling Java Wrapper Files\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">The Java code generator produces a set of files from each component signature, plus a batch file and manifest file used to compile the <span class=\"ph filepath\">.java</span> files into <span class=\"ph filepath\">.class</span> files, and package them into a <span class=\"ph filepath\">.jar</span> file.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section context\" id=\"ixk1665702772151__context_w5904ab1b5b1_w5905ab1b5_w5906ab1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ixk1665702772151__p_d35987e1_d35988e1_d35989e1\">The <span class=\"ph filepath\">.jar</span> file can be imported into a Java development tool, and the JavaBeans integrated into the Java application.</p>\n<div class=\"div context\" id=\"ixk1665702772151__topic_d35990e1_d35991e1_d35992e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ixk1665702772151__p_d35993e1_d35994e1_d35995e1\">To generated, compile, and package Java files:</p>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"ixk1665702772151__li_d18407e1_d18408e1_d18409e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"ixk1665702772151__p_d35996e1_d35997e1_d35998e1\">Generate the Java wrapper source files, batch and\n               manifest files, using the /sto command line switch: </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<p class=\"lines\">/sto/lan=jav {/pth=<var class=\"keyword varname\">Path</var>} {/pkg=<var class=\"keyword varname\">Package</var>} <var class=\"keyword varname\">FileName </var>{<var class=\"keyword varname\">SignatureList </var>}</p>\n<p class=\"p\">For example, the following command line instruction generates files for the\n                  PRODUCT component in the <span class=\"ph filepath\">D:/output</span> directory.</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">idf.exe /sto /lan=jav /path=D:/output /pkg=acme.shop AcmeShop PRODUCT</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ixk1665702772151__p_d35999e1_d36000e1_d36001e1\">Because the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/pkg</span> subswitch is\n                  used, the <span class=\"ph filepath\">.java</span>files are located in the subdirectory\n                     <span class=\"ph filepath\">/acme/shop</span>, and each <span class=\"ph filepath\">.java</span>file\n                  contains the package declaration:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">package acme.shop;</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"ixk1665702772151__note_w5910ab1b5b3b1b3c11_w5911ab1b5b3b1b3_w5912ab1b5b3b1_w5913ab1b5b3_w5914ab1b5_w5915ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> If the Uniface component resides in a Uniface subsystem, the name\n                  derived from the subsystem would be appended to the package name. For example, if\n                  the subsystem name was MY_PROJECT, the resulting package name would be\n                     <code class=\"ph codeph\">acme.shop.my.project</code>.</div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ixk1665702772151__p_d36002e1_d36003e1_d36004e1\">The <span class=\"ph filepath\">AcmeShop.bat</span> and\n                     <span class=\"ph filepath\">AcmeShop.mf</span> files are located in\n                     <span class=\"ph filepath\">D:/output</span>. </p>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"ixk1665702772151__li_d18410e1_d18411e1_d18412e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"ixk1665702772151__p_d36005e1_d36006e1_d36007e1\">Run the generated <span class=\"ph filepath\">.bat</span> to\n               compile the <span class=\"ph filepath\">.java</span> files into <span class=\"ph filepath\">.class</span> files\n               and archive them in a <span class=\"ph filepath\">AcmeShop.jar</span> file. </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">For example, the <span class=\"ph filepath\">AcmeShop.bat</span> file generates the\n                  <span class=\"ph filepath\">AcmeShop.jar</span> file.</div>\n</li></ol></section>\n<section class=\"section result body required-cleanup-multiple-ol-elements-in-topic-body\" id=\"ixk1665702772151__result_w5907ab1b5b5_w5908ab1b5_w5909ab1\">\n<div class=\"sectiondiv postreq\" id=\"ixk1665702772151__topic_d36008e1_d36009e1_d36010e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ixk1665702772151__p_d36011e1_d36012e1_d36013e1\">Import the generated <span class=\"ph filepath\">.jar</span> file into your Java development tool.</p>\n</div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528752\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528752\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Generating and Compiling Java Wrapper Files Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 03, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Generating and Compiling Java Wrapper Files The Java code generator produces a set of files from each component signature, plus a batch file and manifest file used to compile the .java files into .class files, and package them into a .jar file. The .jar file can be imported into a Java development tool, and the JavaBeans integrated into the Java application. To generated, compile, and package Java files: Generate the Java wrapper source files, batch and manifest files, using the /sto command line switch: /sto/lan=jav {/pth= Path } {/pkg= Package } FileName { SignatureList } For example, the following command line instruction generates files for the PRODUCT component in the D:/output directory. idf.exe /sto /lan=jav /path=D:/output /pkg=acme.shop AcmeShop PRODUCT Copy Because the /pkg subswitch is used, the .java files are located in the subdirectory /acme/shop , and each .java file contains the package declaration: package acme.shop; Copy Note: If the Uniface component resides in a Uniface subsystem, the name derived from the subsystem would be appended to the package name. For example, if the subsystem name was MY_PROJECT, the resulting package name would be acme.shop.my.project . The AcmeShop.bat and AcmeShop.mf files are located in D:/output . Run the generated .bat to compile the .java files into .class files and archive them in a AcmeShop.jar file. For example, the AcmeShop.bat file generates the AcmeShop.jar file. Import the generated .jar file into your Java development tool. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}